'''Meritech Capital Partners''' is a [[private equity]] firm focused on [[venture capital|late stage venture capital]] investments in information technology companies with a focus on consumer Internet and media, software and services, enterprise infrastructure, and medical devices.
The [[Palo Alto, California]]-based firm, was founded in 1999 with sponsorship from [[Accel Partners]], [[Oak Investment Partners]], [[Redpoint Ventures]] and Worldview Technology Partners. Since 2003, however, Meritech has independently operated and invested in later stage technology companies. The firm has raised approximately $2.6 billion since inception across four funds.
Among Meritech's most notable investments are Cornerstone OnDemand,<ref>[http://www.cornerstoneondemand.com/2009-3-12-cornerstone-ondemand-secures-new-financing-accelerate-business-growth]</ref> [[Facebook]],<ref>[http://sanfrancisco.bizjournals.com/sanfrancisco/stories/2006/04/17/daily32.html Facebook raises $25M]. San Francisco Business Times, April 19, 2006</ref> [[Fortinet]], and Salesforce.com. Other notable investments include [[2Wire]], [[Sourcefire]], [[Riverbed Technology|Riverbed]], [[Netezza]], [[Netsuite]], [[IntraLase]], and [[Cloudera]].
